Press Win + R → type:

sysdm.cpl


Go to Advanced → Environment Variables

Under User variables for jnasw (recommended), select Path → Edit → New and add:

C:\Program Files\nodejs\
C:\Users\jnasw\AppData\Roaming\npm


(If Path is not there in User variables, add them under System variables → Path instead.)

Click OK on everything.

Close all terminals (PowerShell/VS Code) and reopen PowerShell.

Verify:

npm -v
node -v


Then:

npm run dev

Why it worked yesterday but not today

Most likely PATH got modified/reset (Windows update, reinstall/uninstall of Node, or some software overwrote PATH). Your manual $env:Path += ... worked because it temporarily fixes PATH only for that terminal session.

One quick thing about your last command

In PowerShell, where might not run the way you expect (it can be an alias). Use this instead:

where.exe node
where.exe npm
